A telecommunications company, 9mobile, is set to empower the Small and Medium-scale Enterprises in and around Lagos at its quarterly business networking and empowerment platform, Market Access. Market Access organised in partnership with the Enterprise Development Centre of the Pan Atlantic University is a platform for the SME owners to interact with large corporations with the objective of sharing knowledge and strategies that can enable the growth of start-ups and small businesses. According to a statement from the organisers, the Lagos edition is themed ‘Access to Sustainable Market for SMEs: Challenges and Opportunities.’ The statement quoted the Director, Enterprise Market Segment, 9mobile, Plato Syrimis, as saying that the event empowered potential entrepreneurs by facilitating opportunities for them to network and share knowledge/ideas as this was an important driver towards achieving their individual goals.